President Obama and Dr. Jill Biden will honor the 2011 National Teacher of the Year and State Teachers of the Year. The President believes that education is critical to the nation's success in the global economy, and he wants to inspire innovation and raise graduation rates. Dr. Jill Biden, who has been an educator for 30 years, will host a reception honoring the State Teachers of the Year. The National Teacher of the Year is chosen from among the State Teachers of the Year by a national selection committee. Members of the media who want to cover the Teacher of the Year ceremony must contact the White House. The President will deliver remarks honoring the Teacher of the Year in the Rose Garden. The article also lists the names and schools of the 2011 State Teachers of the Year from each state.